modules.description: Tracks dynamic values that update in response to events, supporting reactive updates through a system of dependent computations. It operates on streams and signals, enabling real-time data flow management. Used to create interactive terminal interfaces by synchronizing user input with visual output.

Provides operations to construct and manipulate formatted text layouts, including line breaks, indentation, and conditional formatting. Works with a custom type `t` representing structured text elements. Used to generate UI components with precise control over spacing and layout, such as formatting error messages or structured output.
